{
  "_comment": [
    "WIN-SYS-002 -- export flows including PDF. Composition-PINNING contract (calc-chrome /",
    "WIN-CA-001 pattern) over the real PDF export tabbed dialog. The PDF options dialog is a",
    "data-driven SfxTabDialogController: filter/source/pdf/impdialog.cxx builds it from",
    "filter/ui/pdfoptionsdialog.ui (a GtkNotebook 'tabcontrol', tab-pos=left) and AddTabPage",
    "composes the pages in a fixed order (general, initialview, userinterface, links, security,",
    "digitalsignatures), each bound to its own page .ui root, with the footer action-widgets",
    "ok(Export,-5) / cancel(-6) / help(-11).",
    "",
    "Its Material treatment is delivered entirely by shared vcl parts already in definition.xml",
    "(tabitem / tabheader / tabpane / tabbody / windowbackground / frame) consumed by the generic",
    "SfxTabDialogController -- there is NO PDF-specific Material paint to add that a build-free",
    "check could honestly verify. So the M-scope is *pinning composition*: the notebook + footer",
    "order in the .ui, the exact ordered AddTabPage tab-id sequence and each tab->page.ui/root-id",
    "binding in impdialog.cxx, each page's ordered GtkFrame group labels, and the native tab/frame/",
    "dialog parts + metrics + both-palette color roles those all resolve through -- every element",
    "fail-closed against drift. The checker also cross-checks that the input-collecting export",
    "dialogs stay native-exclusion (KeepModal) in dialog-notification-policy.csv (read-only), so",
    "the sheet can never be reclassified out of the modal-input guard.",
    "",
    "Everything requiring a build stays OUT and is carved out spec-only: the tab-pos=left icon-rail",
    "geometry (definition.xml declares no rail-width metric), the security/signing per-field anatomy",
    "beyond frame grouping, and all non-PDF export formats (EPUB/XHTML -- deferred to future",
    "WIN-SYS-002 sub-rows). runtime_verified is false: no native build, tab-rail pixels, or runtime",
    "interaction are claimed."
  ],
  "schema_version": 1,
  "contract": "material-pdf-export-dialog-composition",
  "platform": "windows",
  "definition_file": "vcl/uiconfig/theme_definitions/material/definition.xml",
  "theme_flag": "VCL_FILE_WIDGET_THEME",
  "status": "source-declared",
  "runtime_verified": false,
  "design_reference": "docs/design/08-dialogs.md (8.6 Export options -- tabbed dialog (PDF))",
  "impl_source": "filter/source/pdf/impdialog.cxx",
  "dialog_ui": "filter/uiconfig/ui/pdfoptionsdialog.ui",
  "notebook": {
    "id": "tabcontrol",
    "tab_pos": "left"
  },
  "footer": {
